{{Orphan|date=March 2016}}

'''Proformative''' is a free ([[online community]]) for finance professionals<ref>[http://searchfinancialapplications.techtarget.com/feature/Proformative-CEO-aims-to-foster-Yelp-like-hub-for-finance-tech Proformative CEO aims to foster Yelp-like hub for finance tech]</ref>  that is based in ([[Silicon Valley]]). It was incorporated in 2009 by John Kogan and Greg Stout to provide a global online community of senior level ([[corporate finance]]), ([[accounting]]), ([[treasury]]) and related professionals such as CFOs, controllers, treasurers and the like.

Users of the community share knowledge on a wide variety of questions that are commonly faced by such professionals, including ([[leadership]]), ([[technical accounting]]) and finance topics, ([[career management]]), and purchasing of high value products and services. Proformative has over 20,000 user-generated questions, answers and resources and is used by CFOs of public and privately held companies as well as practitioners at every level of such corporations.

Community users often reference other professional and industrial journals suchas [[CFO (magazine)]] and [[Treasury & Risk]].

Proformative reaches over 600,000 such professionals a month and is highly ranked on ([[Alexa Internet|Alexa]]) for its website traffic.

== History ==
Proformative was incorporated in 2009 by John Kogan and Greg Stout. The co-founders have background in corporate finance and scalable web architectures, respectively. Their goal was to provide a global (online community) for ([[CFO]])s, ([[Comptroller|controllers]]), ([[treasurers]]) and the like that was free, “noise free” (no ads), and peer-to-peer so that knowledge could easily be shared between operating professionals in a trusted environment.

On June 20, 2013, Proformative announced an addition to their community platform focused on Enterprise Social Procurement for the office of the CFO.<ref>[http://www.treasuryandrisk.com/2013/06/20/social-procurement-platform-for-the-enterprise "Social Procurement" Platform for the Enterprise]</ref><ref>[http://online.wsj.com/article/PR-CO-20130617-905511.html Proformative Launches Enterprise Social Procurement Platform for the Office of the CFO]</ref><ref>[http://www.treasuryandrisk.com/2013/06/27/new-tools-help-finance-hireand-get-hired New Tools Help Finance Hire—and Get Hired]</ref> The platform provides peer-based reviews of products and services commonly purchased by corporate finance, accounting, treasury and related professionals. Examples include ([[Enterprise resource planning|ERP]]), ([[budgeting]]) & ([[forecasting]]), ([[audit]]) services, ([[liability insurance]]) and others in dozens of product and service categories.

